<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="1021" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1021">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/11–2845: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-28T17:00:00-05:00">November
                                    28, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2409. Deptel 2359 Nov. 17.<note n="19" xml:id="d1021fn1">Not printed; it
                                was similar to telegram 2123, November 17, to Rome, <ref target="#pg_1087">p. 1087</ref>.</note> In connection with
                            revision of Ital armistice regime pls inform FonOff that, on basis of
                            Potsdam agreement re French participation in Ital peace treaty,<note n="20" xml:id="d1021fn2">See Protocol of the Proceedings of the
                                Berlin Conference, section I, (3) (ii), <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1478">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Potsdam</hi>), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp.
                                    1478</ref>, <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1479">1479</ref>.</note> we are of opinion France should be regarded as
                            “signatory power” for armistice revision and inquire whether Soviet Govt
                            concurs in this view.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>